name: Warm Artichoke and Crab Dip
author: lindseyz
summary: This dish is a great appetizer to bring to any family event or holiday party. This yummy dip leaves your taste buds jumping for joy and your friends begging for the recipe! Serve with toasted sliced baguettes, crackers, or tortilla chips.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, room temperature
1 (14 ounce) can artichoke hearts, drained and chopped
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, and onion in a bowl using a hand mixer
Gently fold artichoke hearts and imitation crab, Monterey Jack cheese, and Parmesan cheese into the cream cheese mixture; spread into a pie plate
Bake in preheated oven until browned and bubbling on top, 15 to 20 minutes
